genresAdvancedInfo.name: nz gangsta rap
genresAdvancedInfo.description: NZ Gangsta Rap is a subgenre of hip hop that emerged in New Zealand in the 1990s. It is characterized by its aggressive lyrics, heavy use of profanity, and depictions of street life and gang activity. The genre often features hard-hitting beats and samples from classic funk and soul records. NZ Gangsta Rap has been controversial for its portrayal of violence and drug use, but has also been praised for its raw and authentic depiction of life in urban New Zealand.
